 Based on my analysis, here are some practical curl examples for controlling your Sony Bravia
   TV through the gateway:

  ðŸ“¡ Gateway TV Remote Control - Curl Examples

  API Endpoint Format

  POST /api/users/{user_id}/devices/{device_id}/action

  Basic Remote Control Commands

  1. Power Control

  # Power toggle
  curl -X POST "http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/devices/living_room_tv/action" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{
      "type": "remote",
      "action": "power",
      "parameters": {}
    }'

  # Power on
  curl -X POST "http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/devices/living_room_tv/action" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{
      "type": "remote",
      "action": "power_on",
      "parameters": {}
    }'

  # Power off
  curl -X POST "http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/devices/living_room_tv/action" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{
      "type": "remote",
      "action": "power_off",
      "parameters": {}
    }'

  2. Volume Control

